\n      <td>18.234449</td>\n      <td>17.899447</td>\n      <td>17.616185</td>\n      <td>0.555761</td>\n      <td>M</td>\n      <td>Red_Sequence</td>\n      <td>GALAXY</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n</div>"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":2},{"id":"md-features","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Physics-informed feature engineering\n\nSDSS photometry gives five magnitude bands (`u, g, r, i, z`) plus `redshift`, plate/MJD/fiber metadata, and derived RA/Dec. The features that actually separate STAR / GALAXY / QSO physically are:\n\n- **Color indices** (`u-g, g-r, r-i, i-z, u-z`) — these trace the spectral energy distribution shape; quasars and stars occupy very different loci in color-color space than galaxies.\n- **Redshift transforms** — galaxies and especially quasars have measurable redshift; stars (same galaxy) cluster near `redshift ≈ 0`. Log/sign/binned transforms help tree models split cleanly.\n- **Magnitude ratios & sums** — total brightness and band ratios add information beyond raw magnitudes alone.\n- **PCA color axis** — SDSS's own `u-g` vs `g-r` star/galaxy/QSO locus separation, approximated via a rotated color-color combination.\n\nThis cell only uses columns that exist in the dataframe — if a column is missing it's skipped safely.","metadata":{}},{"id":"cell-02-fe","cell_type":"code","source":"BANDS = ['u', 'g', 'r', 'i', 'z']\n\ndef add_physics_features(df):\n    df = df.copy()\n    present = [b for b in BANDS if b in df.columns]\n\n    # Color indices (adjacent + cross bands)\n    for a, b in zip(present, present[1:]):\n        df[f'{a}_{b}_color'] = df[a] - df[b]\n    if 'u' in present and 'z' in present:\n        df['u_z_color'] = df['u'] - df['z']\n    if 'g' in present and 'i' in present:\n        df['g_i_color'] = df['g'] - df['i']\n\n    # Aggregate brightness stats\n    if len(present) >= 3:\n        df['mag_mean'] = df[present].mean(axis=1)\n        df['mag_std']  = df[present].std(axis=1)\n        df['mag_range'] = df[present].max(axis=1) - df[present].min(axis=1)\n        df['mag_sum'] = df[present].sum(axis=1)\n\n    # Pairwise ratios for the strongest discriminating bands\n    if 'u' in present and 'g' in present:\n        df['u_g_ratio'] = df['u'] / (df['g'].replace(0, np.nan))\n    if 'r' in present and 'i' in present:\n        df['r_i_ratio'] = df['r'] / (df['i'].replace(0, np.nan))\n\n    # Redshift transforms — primary QSO/GALAXY vs STAR separator\n    if 'redshift' in df.columns:\n        df['redshift_abs'] = df['redshift'].abs()\n        df['redshift_log1p'] = np.sign(df['redshift']) * np.log1p(df['redshift'].abs())\n        df['redshift_is_near_zero'] = (df['redshift'].abs() < 1e-3).astype(np.int8)\n        df['redshift_sq'] = df['redshift'] ** 2\n        # Color-redshift interactions (color evolves with redshift for galaxies/QSOs)\n        if 'g_r_color' in df.columns:\n            df['color_x_redshift'] = df['g_r_color'] * df['redshift']\n\n    # Rotated color-color axis approximating the SDSS star/galaxy/QSO locus split\n    if 'u_g_color' in df.columns and 'g_r_color' in df.columns:\n        theta = np.deg2rad(35)\n        df['locus_axis1'] = (df['u_g_color'] * np.cos(theta) + df['g_r_color'] * np.sin(theta))\n        df['locus_axis2'] = (-df['u_g_color'] * np.sin(theta) + df['g_r_color'] * np.cos(theta))\n\n    # Positional features (some objects cluster spatially by survey plate)\n    if 'plate' in df.columns:\n        df['plate_mod'] = df['plate'] % 100\n    if 'fiber_id' in df.columns:\n        df['fiber_log'] = np.log1p(df['fiber_id'])\n\n    df.replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan, inplace=True)\n    return df\n\ntrain_fe = add_physics_features(train)\ntest_fe  = add_physics_features(test)\n\ndrop_cols = [ID, TARGET]\nfeature_cols = [c for c in train_fe.columns if c not in drop_cols]\nfeature_cols = [c for c in feature_cols if train_fe[c].dtype != object]\n\nprint(f'Total engineered features: {len(feature_cols)}')\nprint(feature_cols)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"executi